IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: TO ORGANIZE, MANAGE, AND MAINTAIN A SYMPHONY ORCHESTRA FOR THE CULTURAL BENEFIT OF THE PUBLIC AND PARTICULARLY THE COMMUNITY OF LANCASTER COUNTY THROUGH THE PRESENTATION OF MUSICAL PROGRAMS AND CONCERTS. THE SYMPHONY ALSO PROVIDES A SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM FOR STUDENTS INTERESTED IN PURSUING STUDIES IN THE FIELD OF MUSIC. THE SYMPHONY ALSO HOLDS SYMPHONIC CONCERTS FOR CHILDREN IN GRADES THREE THROUGH FIVE FREE OF CHARGE TO INTRODUCE YOUNGSTERS TO A SYMPHONY ORCHESTRA AND ARE USED BY MUSIC EDUCATORS AS A SPRINGBOARD INTO INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15b: Compensation Review and Approval Process for Officers and Key Employees
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: BOARD LEADERSHIP AND THE CHAIR OF THE PERSONNEL COMMITTEE MEETS WITH THE MUSIC DIRECTOR TO DISCUSS GOALS, ACCOMPLISHMENTS AND OPPORTUNITIES FOR IMPROVEMENT ON AN ANNUAL BASIS. INDUSTRY COMPENSATION DATA IS AVAILABLE THROUGH THE LEAGUE OF AMERICAN ORCHESTRAS.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS SIGNED BY THE BOARD ANNUALLY.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11: Form 990 Review Process
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE MANAGEMENT TEAM REVIEWS THE FORM 990 DRAFT PRIOR TO ISSUING. THE AUDIT COMMITTEE REVIEWS THE FINAL FORM 990 AND PRESENTS IT FOR REVIEW AND DISCUSSION AT THE BOARD'S FINANCE COMMITTEE. THE FINANCE COMMITTEE MAKES A RECOMMENDATION TO THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS TO ACCEPT THE FORM 990 AND PROVIDES A 30-DAY OPPORTUNITY FOR ANY INDIVIDUAL BOARD MEMBER TO REVIEW THE DOCUMENT AND ASK QUESTIONS. THE FULL BOARD VOTES TO ACCEPT THE FORM 990 AT THE NEXT MEETING.
